    - The 'eyes and ears official' (이목관) refers to an imperial inspector charged with maintaining order and reporting directly to the throne.
    - The 'three Han' (삼한) refers to the three ancient Korean kingdoms—Goguryeo, Baekje, and Silla—and by extension, the Korean people as a whole.
    - The memorial invokes the Doctrine of the Mean (중용) to argue for preserving Goryeo's traditional status within the Yuan administrative system, appealing to principles of benevolent governance.
